President Donald Trump has been working to foster bipartisan unity and support through meetings with Senators at the White House. He recently hosted a bipartisan dinner with Senators Joe Donnelly, Orrin Hatch, Joe Manchin, John Thune, Heidi Heitkamp, and Pat Toomey to discuss tax cuts for middle-class Americans. Trump also met with Senator Tim Scott to discuss his response to the protests in Charlottesville and race relations in the US. Additionally, he welcomed 13 House members to the White House to continue the tax reform discussion. Trump also had a bipartisan dinner with Senator Chuck Schumer and Congresswoman Nancy Pelosi to discuss the upcoming legislative agenda. The administration is focused on delivering tax relief to the American people and promoting economic growth.